<li><a href="http://www.ejhs.org/volume5/polyoutline.html" class="external text" title="http://www.ejhs.org/volume5/polyoutline.html" rel="nofollow">Working with polyamorous clients in the clinical setting</a> - Davidson (Volume 5, April 16, 2002, also delivered to the Society for the Scientific Study of Sexuality, Western Regional Conference, April 2002)</li>
<li><a href="http://www.ejhs.org/volume6/polyamory.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.ejhs.org/volume6/polyamory.htm" rel="nofollow">Polyamory - What it is and what it isn't</a> - McCullough and Hall (Volume 6, February 27, 2003)</li>
<li><a href="http://www.ejhs.org/volume8/cook1.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.ejhs.org/volume8/cook1.htm" rel="nofollow">Commitment in polyamory</a> - Cook (Volume 8, December 12, 2005)</li>
