<li id="cite_note-ILIC-6">^ <a href="#cite_ref-ILIC_6-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-ILIC_6-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-ILIC_6-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-ILIC_6-3" title=""><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-ILIC_6-4" title=""><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREF.5Bhttp:.2F.2Fwww.hevanet.com.2Falexwest.2Fmail_me.html_West.2C_Alex.5D"><a href="http://www.hevanet.com/alexwest/mail_me.html" class="external text" title="http://www.hevanet.com/alexwest/mail_me.html" rel="nofollow">West, Alex</a> (<span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2001-02-06"><a href="/wiki/2001" title="2001">2001</a>-<a href="/wiki/February_6" title="February 6">02-06</a></span>). <a href="http://www.hevanet.com/alexwest/parrots/symbolist.html" class="external text" title="http://www.hevanet.com/alexwest/parrots/symbolist.html" rel="nofollow">"A List of Poly Symbols"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.hevanet.com/alexwest/parrots/symbolist.html" class="external free" title="http://www.hevanet.com/alexwest/parrots/symbolist.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.hevanet.com/alexwest/parrots/symbolist.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2002-05-11</span>.  "variations on Pi-and-the-three-colors the ILIC symbol. ... The symbol that started this category, Jim Evans' Poly Pride Flag. He has put this image in the public domain. ... "ILIC" stands for Infinite Love in Infinite Combinations (a reference to Star Trek's IDIC credo --- the D in the Star Trek version stands for "Diversity"). When I first listed this symbol, I did not have a copy of this image archived locally (even though the author said on his site that the symbol was public domain)"</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=A+List+of+Poly+Symbols&